Key Insights & Analysis

  • Health Impact: Average of 6.7 estimated respiratory cases per day
  • Pollution Levels: PM2.5 average of 55.3 µg/m³ (exceeds WHO guidelines)
  • Primary Correlate: PM10 (ug/m3) shows strongest correlation (r = 0.318)
  • Data Quality: 100.0% complete

Key Characteristics

  • Environmental health crisis (high COPD in non-smokers). Pediatric respiratory emergency (10x normal rates)
  • Severe seasonal patterns (post-Diwali surges)
  • Growing medical tourism. Excellent medical institutions (KGMU, RMLIMS, SGPGIMS)
  • Lucknow demonstrates how even healthcare hubs face severe environmental health crises

    *Synthetic Data Considerations

  • Population: ~4.13M (metro 2025); literacy 82.50%; sex ratio 928/1000
  • Respiratory Disease: High burden—COPD 8.5% among rural non-smokers (3x national average); recent surge with 25-30% of pediatric patients having respiratory ailments vs usual 2-3%
  • Healthcare: Major medical institutions (KGMU, RMLIMS, SGPGIMS) with Rs 531 crore infrastructure boost; healthcare sector grew 25% over 5 years; emerging medical tourism hub
  • Seasonal Patterns: Strong winter peaks (75.5 vs 53.11 per 1000 in summer); post-Diwali respiratory surge; strong PM2.5 correlation (r=0.94)
  • Socioeconomic: State capital; UP is India's 3rd largest economy growing at 7% CAGR; major administrative and healthcare center
